The paper deals with iris recognition using deep learning models, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper examines the impact of segmentation on recognition performance, which is related to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of iris recognition, which is related to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
